    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Every year in the shadowed weeks of the Red Harvest, when the fields lie fallow and folk light lanterns carved from turnips, you’ll find barrels of blood potion hauled out from cellars and cellared caves. Despite its name, there’s not a drop of true blood in the drink. It’s a thick, jewel-red brew made from cherries or dark forest berries, boiled down into a syrupy kompot and spiced with cloves, cinnamon bark, and sometimes a splash of vinegar to give it a bite sharp enough to wake the dead.</p>",
